From Subject Re Harry Caray In article Bernard O'Dell writes Being an old time Cardinal Fan now relocated to the NVA area I can recall that Harry was not at all popular with old man Busch who as I understand it fired him and kicked him out of I am not quite sure of the reasons but the old man was certainly not enraptured by ole Bern O'Dell I grew up listening to Harry Carey call the Cardinals' games and really liked him But as I recall he was fired because he was too critical read honest when he was He dared to point out the Cards' miscues and At least this is what I remember from when I was a Kay Jones